----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Switch to port 5358

Installation:

git clone https://github.com/dpengineering/avahi_0.8

Kill avahi-daemon:
```
sudo systemctl stop avahi-daemon.service avahi-daemon.socket
sudo apt purge avahi-daemon
```
Install dependencies:
```
sudo apt install build-essential manpages-dev libevent-dev qtbase5-dev mono-mcs monodoc-http
sudo apt-get build-dep avahi
```
*If sudp apt-get build-dep avahi throws an error along the lines of E: You must put some 'source' URIs in your sources.list run:
```
sudo cp /etc/apt/sources.list /etc/apt/sources.list~
sudo sed -Ei 's/^# deb-src /deb-src /' /etc/apt/sources.list
sudo apt-get update
```
Compile:

`./autogen.sh && sudo make && sudo make install`

Check if avahi user is present and is a part of the group avahi:
`less /etc/passwd`

If not present add user,
`sudo adduser --disabled-password --quiet --system         --home /var/run/avahi-daemon         --gecos "Avahi mDNS daemon" --group avahi`

Add the dbus conf file:
`cp avahi-dbus.conf /etc/dbus-1/system.d/avahi-dbus.conf`
